The article is about the sudden death of Jim Crown, who was described as a thoughtful, warm, and good man. Jim had a remarkable life story, starting as the great-grandson of a sweatshop worker and eventually becoming a successful business and civic leader in Chicago. He was deeply committed to his city and made significant contributions to various institutions. Jim was also working on a new initiative to address gun violence and promote hiring from marginalized communities. He was seen as a representation of the best of America - hardworking, compassionate, and always looking out for others. The author expresses their condolences to Jim's family and describes him as a dear friend and a great American.